Writing A Book Using Git: How Git Can Keep You Organized On A Project

Perks of Writing in Git
    - More detailed version history than any word processing software
    - Transparency - comments don't vanish like in Google Docs or Word
    - Designed to be used by multiple people in different stages of the process

Brainstorming and Organizing
    - Kanban Boards as a brainstorming technique
        - she made one set of cards per theme in the book
        - then she turned these into flash cards (physical) to organize her chapters
        - then chapter outline in Kanban

Editing book in Git
    - the editor would make a pull request for anything they wanted to change (and changed)
